cs.CR, cs.AR, cs.IT, cs.CE, cs.ET

The paper discusses the development of a lattice cryptography processor for resource-constrained IoT devices, which involves aspects of cryptography (cs.CR), computer architecture (cs.AR), information theory (cs.IT), computer engineering (cs.CE), and electronic devices (cs.ET). Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CR, followed by cs.AR, cs.IT, cs.CE, and cs.ET.
